opic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 2h hammers?</span><hr size=1> Anyone able to tell me where I can buy these of a merchant in Midgard?<br><br>Asterid<br>Skald Percival <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uhamlet3145.showPublicProfile?language=EN>hamlet3145</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/30/02 10:04:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mchsi.com/~macleod991/hamlet2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h hammers?</span><hr size=1> What level are you?<br><br>Saga is the 2 hand weapon merchant in Jordheim.  He's under the tarp near all the viking trainers.<br><br>Also, at higher levs you can buy magical hammers in Darkness Falls.<br><br>And don't forget crafter made weapons--I've killed many a werewolf with a 98% qual Dwarven Great Sword. =) <p>---------------------------------------------- <BR><b>Hamlet Songbringer--Norse Skald</b> <BR</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ubeverlyvargdatter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Beverly Vargdatter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/30/02 10:24:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h hammers?</span><hr size=1> Ah must just have missed it then..I bought a 2h sword to try out with but haven't trained any of the styles yet and decided I'd go for crush.<br>I'm a lvl 5 btw,have a 16 thane on Percival too and a 32 albion cleric on Bedevere as my other mains.<br><br>Asterid <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ufubbor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fubbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ff0000>(4/30/02 5:18:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2h hammers?</span><hr size=1> Hammer of Black Ice <br>15.0 dps 5.3 speed <br>100% quality <br>25% bonus <br>+4 hammer <br>+7 str <br>+15 Hits <br>has a 88+ energy proc <br>comes from drunk dwarf quest <br><br>Soul Forge <br>16.2 dps 5.4 speed <br>91% quality <br>25% bonus <br>+6 hammer <br>+4 parry <br>has a 97+ energy proc <br>I got mine from Yar but I hear it can drop off other werewolves around dragon lair <br><br>Brilliant Baln's Mephitic Bludge <br>16.2 dps 5.0 speed <br>94% quality <br>25% bonus <br>+3 hammer <br>+3 parry <br>+10 str <br>+9 quickness <br>has a 56 point dex/quick 15 seconds Debuff proc <br>I got this last nite off Prince in darkness falls <br><br><br>Im still testing but from what I have seen so far: <br>Black ice still hits the hardest because of the 100% quality. But its a bit slow, the stats arnt that great and it dont seem to proc as much or as hard as Soul Forge. <br><br>Soul Forge has good stats the proc is great and it can do good damage. Again at 5.4 speed if you dont have haste or quick buffs it is really slow. <br><br>Brilliant Baln's Mephitic Bludge, I am still testing this one since I just got it but the damage is between black ice and soul forge. At 5.0 speed its really fast. But im not sure how good this debuff proc really is as of right now there is no graphix effect for the proc. But on the plus side there is a really cool graphix for the hammer its self It looks alot like level 40 epic hammer but it has a bright blue glowing ball of light on the end. <br><br><br>would also like to add the hammer from saphire vendor in darkness I am useing this one alot now dont have specs atm but its pretty fast and has a fire base proc that hits for 100+ and it's only like 50 some sapphire seals so you can beat on keep doors and stuff and get a new one easy. <p>Icebane  50 Skald Lancelot,</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugainsward2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gainsward2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/3/02 2:35:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lvl 13 and a good Magic hammer?</span><hr size=1> Suggestions on where I can get a good magiccal hammer that I can use at Lvl 13 and perhaps to 18 or 20?<br><br><br>Gird<br>Dwarven Skald<br>Lvl 13 Gawayne <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradon>Aradon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/7/02 6:37:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.jollyjokers.com/daoc/memberimages/raven.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lvl 13 and a good Magic hammer?</span><hr size=1> Best Hammers (for RvR Endgame) are the p